<div class="content-section">
<h2>What Function Health actually is</h2>
<p>Function Health, co-founded by Dr. Mark Hyman and Jonathan Swerdlin and backed by $298 million in Series B financing (raised November 2025), is a direct-to-consumer biomarker testing platform built around the premise that the data underlying most serious disease begins accumulating years before diagnosis &#8212; and that consumers should be able to see it without waiting for a physician to order it.</p>
<p>The membership includes two comprehensive blood draws per year at Quest Diagnostics locations. The first draw covers the full 100+ marker panel. The mid-year follow-up covers the roughly 60 most clinically significant markers &#8212; enough to detect meaningful changes from interventions made after the first draw. Results are delivered through a polished dashboard with per-marker explanations, flagged values, a clinician review process, and a personalized protocol. An AI-assisted protocol builder is in beta as of early 2026.</p>

<div class="callout">
<div class="callout-label">No affiliate relationship</div>
<p>AgelessLabs does not currently have an affiliate relationship with Function Health. This review is included because it&#8217;s one of the most-searched services in our audience, and an honest comparison requires covering it. If you decide to purchase, a referral link from a current member typically unlocks $25 off.</p>
</div>
</div>

