<p>For à la carte testing without a subscription, the <a href="/reviews/ulta-lab-tests">Ulta Lab Tests review</a> covers the direct-to-consumer alternative. For the detailed head-to-head with Superpower, see our <a href="/reviews/superpower-health">Superpower Health review</a>.</p>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
<h2>Who Function Health is right for</h2>
<p>Function Health is the right choice if you&#8217;re actively managing a cardiovascular, hormonal, or metabolic health issue and need to track response to interventions across the year. The twice-yearly draw is the key &#8212; if you only need a single annual snapshot, Superpower at $199 is the better value. If you want cancer marker or heavy metal screening alongside your biomarker panel, Function is the only service in this price category that offers it.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s also the right choice for anyone who wants the most defensible, complete picture of their health &#8212; all direct measurements, clinician review on flagged values, and the broadest marker coverage available outside of a concierge medicine practice.</p>
<p>Where it falls short: if you have existing years of lab data you want to integrate, Superpower&#8217;s historical import feature is a meaningful practical advantage. And if budget is the primary constraint, Superpower&#8217;s $199 covers the longevity fundamentals at two-thirds the price.</p>
</div>

