<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-list">
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is Function Health worth it in 2026?</div>
<div class="faq-answer">At $365/year, yes &#8212; particularly if you&#8217;re actively managing health markers or want the ability to retest mid-year. Two draws, 160+ directly measured markers, cancer screening, and heavy metals make it the most complete consumer panel available. If a single annual snapshot covers your needs, <a href="/reviews/superpower-health">Superpower at $199</a> is the better value.</div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How does Function Health compare to Superpower?</div>
<div class="faq-answer">Function is $166/year more with two annual draws, 160+ direct measurements, and coverage Superpower doesn&#8217;t offer (cancer markers, heavy metals, ANA, Lp(a) and omega-3 index in base panel). Superpower&#8217;s advantages are lower price, a more polished AI chat, and historical lab import. If you&#8217;re tracking an active intervention, Function&#8217;s second draw makes the price difference worthwhile. See the <a href="/reviews/superpower-health">Superpower review</a> for the full comparison.</div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What biomarkers does Function Health include?</div>
<div class="faq-answer">160+ directly measured markers including <a href="/biomarkers/apob">ApoB</a>, <a href="/biomarkers/lipoprotein-a">Lp(a)</a>, NMR lipoprofile, full hormone panel, thyroid (TSH + free T3/T4 + reverse T3 + TPO antibodies), cancer markers (PSA, CEA, AFP, CA-125), heavy metals (lead, mercury, arsenic), ANA autoimmune screen, <a href="/biomarkers/omega-3-index">omega-3 index</a>, and complete CBC and CMP.</div>
</div>
